arch:property.oc:show_val: Smallish unit; various size of fragments with both old and modern breaks; mostly sheep and some cattle size animals; mostly head and feet fragments and also some long bone fragments; surface condition of the bones is variable. There are some infantiles--kids/lambs--represented by unfused phalanges; one wild boar astragalus; some microfauna. X3 is a goodly but not huge chunk of cattle horn core. There is little or no gnawing and some digestion. There seem to somewhat mixed origins, but some stuff looks pretty fresh. The unit looks like a small household fill. 4mm %100 sorted. Last number = 117

arch:string.div: The unique identifier for each contextual unit, matching those used in the central Çatalhöyük excavation database and in publications. The excavation uses single-context recording.
